conclusion: Determine the time t1 it takes for the lower end of the wooden rod to reach the upper end A of the cylinder AB.
The wooden rod is 5 meters long, and the upper end is fixed at a point 20 meters above the cylinder.
The lower end of the rod starts 25 meters above point A (20 meters + 5 meters).
Use the kinematic equation for free fall: d = 1/2 g t^2.
g is the acceleration due to gravity, which is 10 m/s^2.
Set up the equation for the lower end reaching point A: 25 = 1/2 * 10 * t1^2.
The time t1 it takes for the lower end of the wooden rod to reach the upper end A of the cylinder is approximately 2.236 seconds.
